{"Body": "\n\nUNIONDALE, N.Y. (AP) -- State police say they're investigating after someone threw a brick onto a New York parkway, smashing a moving car's windshield and injuring a passenger.\n\n\n\nTroopers say Sunday that the brick was tossed onto the Meadowbrook Parkway on Long Island from a pedestrian footbridge just before 8 p.m. Saturday.\n\n\n\nThey say a 22-year-old woman in the passenger seat of a blue 1996 BMW was treated for eye and mouth injuries at a hospital and then released. They say the 21-year-old man driving the car suffered a bruised right shoulder but refused medical attention.\n\n\n\nTroopers say the driver and his passenger called 911 after their windshield was smashed as they drove northbound on the parkway.\n\n\n\nTroopers: Brick smashes car's windwhield on New York parkway", "Title": "Troopers: Brick smashes car's windwhield on New York parkway - - News - Top Stories"}